Package org.red5.io.obu

Class OBUParser

java.lang.Object
org.red5.io.obu.OBUParser
public class OBUParser extends Object
Parsers OBU providing headers and extract relevant data. Logic is derived from the C code in the obuparser project.
Author:
Paul Gregoire

    • startsWithFragment

      public static boolean startsWithFragment(byte aggregationHeader)
      Returns true if the given byte starts a fragment. This is denoted as Z in the spec: MUST be set to 1 if the first OBU element is an OBU fragment that is a continuation of an OBU fragment from the previous packet, and MUST be set to 0 otherwise.
      Parameters:
      aggregationHeader - a byte
      Returns:
      true if the given byte starts a fragment

    • endsWithFragment

      public static boolean endsWithFragment(byte aggregationHeader)
      Returns true if the given byte ends a fragment. This is denoted as Y in the spec: MUST be set to 1 if the last OBU element is an OBU fragment that will continue in the next packet, and MUST be set to 0 otherwise.
      Parameters:
      aggregationHeader - a byte
      Returns:
      true if the given byte ends a fragment

    • startsNewCodedVideoSequence

      public static boolean startsNewCodedVideoSequence(byte aggregationHeader)
      Returns true if the given byte is the starts a new sequence. This denoted as N in the spec: MUST be set to 1 if the packet is the first packet of a coded video sequence, and MUST be set to 0 otherwise.
      Parameters:
      aggregationHeader - a byte
      Returns:
      true if the given byte starts a new sequence
